%U A037492 72697035621002,508879249347015,3562154745429107,24935083218003750,174545582526026252,1221819077682183765
%N A037492 Base 7 digits are, in order, the first n terms of the periodic sequence with initial period 2,1.
%H A037492 <a href="/index/Rec#order_03">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (7,1,-7).
%F A037492 a(n) = 7*a(n-1) + a(n-2) - 7*a(n-3).
%F A037492 G.f.: x*(2+x) / ( (x-1)*(7*x-1)*(1+x) ). - _R. J. Mathar_, Nov 21 2011
%F A037492 a(n) = floor(5*7^n/16). - _Christian Krause_, May 30 2026
%F A037492 E.g.f.: (5*(cosh(7*x) - cosh(x) + sinh(7*x)) - 3*sinh(x))/16. - _Stefano Spezia_, May 30 2026
%K A037492 nonn,base,easy
%O A037492 1,1
